Add sockets end to end. Implement a feature that clearly uses socket.io (server + client) so you can demo real-time behavior.

(Socket.io now wraps Express and maintains a rolling “Study Room” message history, so any client can join and broadcast tips in real time (server/app.js (lines 1-108)). Each connection immediately receives the current history, and the server sanitizes/limits incoming payloads before emitting to everyone.

To support the new UI flow, the auth router exposes a logout endpoint that destroys the session and clears the cookie (server/routers/authRoutes.js (lines 120-129)).

The profile view is now the hub for real-time collaboration: after confirming the session it opens a socket.io-client connection, listens for history + live messages, and renders a chat feed plus send form; logout reuses the new API (client/src/pages/Profile.svelte (lines 1-120)).

Client dependencies include socket.io-client so remember to install/update packages (client/package.json (lines 16-21), run npm install inside client). Restart the server (npm run dev in server) so the new HTTP+Socket.IO setup takes effect, and run the Vite dev server to test chatting between two browsers.




