Why SQLite (informed choice)

Simple setup, no server needed
Works great with small web apps
Easy to inspect manually during exam
Already used in your project
Database commands (run in terminal)

From Eksamen/studyhelp/server, open the DB:
sqlite3 database.db

List tables:
.tables

Show schema:
.schema reminders
.schema users

Insert a reminder manually:
INSERT INTO reminders (user_id, title, reminder_date, reminder_time)
VALUES (1, 'Exam prep', '2026-02-15', '18:00');

List reminders for one user:
SELECT id, title, reminder_date, reminder_time
FROM reminders
WHERE user_id = 1
ORDER BY reminder_date, reminder_time;

Delete a reminder:
DELETE FROM reminders WHERE id = 1;

Exit:
.quit